The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem involving points in Euclidean space, which suggests that it could belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The problem also involves a supply function and transportation maps, which suggests that it could belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The algorithmic approach involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA), as well as information theory (cs.IT) for the analysis of the approximation guarantee. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
